# Post-sprint documentation reconciliation

Read the sprint plan, chunks, manifest, scratchpad, changed files, and existing repository docs.
Update only documentation made stale or incomplete by the sprint. Prefer the repository's existing
canonical locations and style. Do not create a parallel documentation hierarchy or narrate internal
agent activity.

Record what was updated in the sprint directory and append durable documentation decisions or dead
ends to `SCRATCHPAD.md`. If no documentation change is warranted, record the evidence instead of
manufacturing churn.

If you change repository documentation, inspect status, stage only those paths, and create a
descriptive scoped commit before exiting. When `RALPH_STATE_MODE=tracked`, include the documentation
record and scratchpad artifacts; when it is `local`, never stage `.ralph/`.
